  "supp.subj_6": "Other",
  "terms.s1.bundles": "The iOS App is distributed under the bundle identifier com.oakdev.nuria; the Android App is distributed under the package identifier com.oakdev.nuria.android.",
  "terms.s1.eu": "OakDev is established in Sweden. Nuria is therefore subject to Swedish law, applicable European Union consumer-protection directives, and the EU General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR).",
  "terms.s1.intro": "The App is published and operated by:",
  "terms.s1.platforms": "These Terms are entered into between you and OakDev (operating Nuria). Apple Inc. And Google LLC are not parties to these Terms, have no obligation whatsoever to furnish any maintenance or support services with respect to the App, and are not responsible for addressing any claims you may have relating to the App or your use of it. The App store from which you obtained the App is a third-party beneficiary of these Terms only to the limited extent necessary to enforce the platform's own rules; in all other respects, the App store has no rights or obligations under these Terms.",
  "terms.s1.title": "1. Publisher and Contact",
  "terms.s10.intro": "If you reinstall the App, change device, or sign in on a new device, you can re-acknowledge prior purchases by tapping Restore Purchases on the offer screen or Account screen. When you tap Restore:",
  "terms.s10.note": "Restore Purchases is a recovery mechanism, not a duplicate-entitlement mechanism. You may not use it to obtain entitlements on accounts other than the one originally tied to the purchase.",
  "terms.s10.title": "10. Restore Purchases and Device Recovery",
  "terms.s11.1.title": "11.1 Types of notifications",
  "terms.s11.2.body": "Your device's operating system requests permission before Nuria sends push notifications. You may change your preference at any time through device settings (iOS: Settings &rarr; Notifications &rarr; Nuria; Android: Settings &rarr; Apps &rarr; Nuria &rarr; Notifications) or through in-App notification controls.",
  "terms.s11.2.title": "11.2 Permission and control",
  "terms.s11.3.body": "Prayer-time notification scheduling is calculated on-device. We do not receive your GPS coordinates in order to schedule prayer-time notifications. If you set a city or time-zone preference in the App, that preference (not your GPS coordinates) is stored on our servers.",
  "terms.s11.3.title": "11.3 No location transmitted for notifications",
  "terms.s11.title": "11. Push Notifications",
  "terms.s12.1.body": "The Nuria Partner Programme allows Islamic organisations, mosques, community groups, educational institutions, and similar community entities (\"Partners\") to register, receive a unique referral code, and share that code within their community. Users who register using a valid partner referral code may receive a benefit as displayed in the App at the time of registration.",
  "terms.s12.1.title": "12.1 Programme overview",
  "terms.s12.2.body": "Registration is at our sole discretion. We may decline applications from organisations whose values, activities, or content we reasonably consider inconsistent with mainstream Islamic teaching or that present a reputational risk to Nuria or its user community. We may revoke a Partner's code at any time with reasonable notice if circumstances change.",
  "terms.s12.2.title": "12.2 Partner eligibility and registration",
  "terms.s12.3.intro": "Partners must:",
  "terms.s12.3.title": "12.3 Partner obligations",
  "terms.s12.4.body": "Unless a separate written agreement expressly states otherwise, the Partner Programme does not entitle Partners to financial commission, revenue share, or payment of any kind.",
  "terms.s12.4.title": "12.4 No financial compensation by default",
  "terms.s12.5.body": "For programme administration we associate each referral code with the email of a Nuria Partner account. Where verifiable, we record the Firebase Authentication user identifier (UID) for that account. Where we agree to provide payments to a Partner under a separate written agreement, we may collect additional information necessary for payouts (identity and contact details, tax/company identifiers, banking details). Data practices for the Partner Programme are described in our Privacy Policy.",
  "terms.s12.5.title": "12.5 Data, accounts, and operational profiles",
  "terms.s12.6.body": "Partner dashboards, reports, and administrative URLs are confidential. Partners must not share credentials, scrape, probe, or reverse-engineer our systems, or contact end users in violation of our Privacy Policy or applicable law.",
  "terms.s12.6.title": "12.6 Confidentiality of partner tools",
  "terms.s12.7.body": "Where a Partner enters into a separate written agreement with us, that agreement governs the commercial relationship to the extent it expressly overrides these Terms; in case of conflict, the separate agreement prevails only as to its subject matter.",
  "terms.s12.7.title": "12.7 Separate agreements",
  "terms.s12.8.body": "Any attempt to exploit the Partner Programme. Multi-account fraud, fictitious activations, or reverse-engineering attribution. Is prohibited and constitutes a violation of these Terms.",
  "terms.s12.8.title": "12.8 Fraudulent referral use",
  "terms.s12.title": "12. Partner / Affiliate Referral Programme",
  "terms.s13.consequences": "We reserve the right to remove offending content, restrict features, or suspend or terminate accounts in accordance with Section 23.",
  "terms.s13.intro": "You agree to use Nuria only for its intended purpose of personal spiritual guidance, Islamic learning, and reflection. You must not:",
  "terms.s13.title": "13. Acceptable Use and Prohibited Conduct",
  "terms.s14.feedback": "If you provide feedback, suggestions, or bug reports, you grant us a non-exclusive, worldwide, royalty-free, irrevocable, perpetual licence to use, incorporate, and commercialise that feedback without compensation or attribution.",
  "terms.s14.intro": "When you use the App you may author content of various kinds. Including personalised reflections, family tree entries, legacy bequests (text and voice), Halqa circle data, Muhasaba self-accountability journal entries, profile information, your Nuria code, preferences, and feedback (collectively, \"Your Content\").",
  "terms.s14.noPublic": "This licence does not include a public-display right. We will not publicly display, publish, sell, or otherwise commercialise Your Content. The licence terminates when Your Content is deleted from our systems, subject to lawful retention for backups, security logs, or where required by law.",
  "terms.s14.ownership": "You retain ownership of Your Content. You grant us a worldwide, non-exclusive, royalty-free, sublicensable (only to our service providers acting on our behalf), operational licence to host, store, transmit, process, back up, restore, encrypt, format, and otherwise technically handle Your Content solely for the purpose of operating, maintaining, securing, and providing the App and its features to you and to the recipients you designate (for example, to deliver a legacy bequest to a designated family member).",
  "terms.s14.responsibility": "You represent and warrant that Your Content does not violate the rights of any third party and complies with these Terms and applicable law. You are responsible for what you write.",
  "terms.s14.title": "14. User-Generated Content and Licence to Nuria",
  "terms.s15.1.body": "All aspects of the App. Design, user interface, graphics, illustrations, logos, text, software code, algorithms, trade marks (\"Nuria\", \"Barakah\", \"Luxury Stone\", and related marks), database rights, and the selection, arrangement, and presentation of content. Are the property of OakDev or its licensors and are protected by copyright, trade mark, database, and other intellectual property laws in Sweden and internationally.",
  "terms.s15.1.title": "15.1 Our intellectual property",
  "terms.s15.2.body": "Subject to your compliance with these Terms, we grant you a limited, personal, non-exclusive, non-transferable, non-sublicensable, revocable licence to install and use the App on devices you own or control, solely for your own personal, non-commercial Islamic spiritual development and learning. This licence does not grant you any right to sublicense, resell, reproduce for distribution, modify, or create derivative works from the App or any of its content.",
  "terms.s15.2.title": "15.2 Licence granted to you",
  "terms.s15.3.body": "Quranic verses, Hadith, and other Islamic scholarly content referenced in the App are drawn from the public domain of Islamic scholarship and are used solely for religious education, worship, and spiritual guidance. Nuria makes no claim of ownership over any sacred Islamic text. All Quranic content is presented with the utmost care, reverence, and respect for the sanctity of the Word of Allah &#65018;.",
  "terms.s15.3.title": "15.3 Islamic texts",
  "terms.s15.4.body": "Reflections and Ask Nuria answers produced through the App are delivered to you for your personal, private spiritual use only. To the extent any intellectual property rights may arise in such generated content, OakDev or its licensors retain those rights. You may not reproduce, publish, distribute, broadcast, sublicense, or commercialise generated content.",
  "terms.s15.4.title": "15.4 Generated reflection and Ask Nuria content",
  "terms.s15.title": "15. Intellectual Property and Licence to You",
  "terms.s16.body": "The spiritual content provided through Nuria. Including reflections, role-model profiles, daily Islamic guidance, Hadith content, Quranic content, tafsir, Qaida lessons, Sunnat material, and educational features. Is provided for personal spiritual enrichment and Islamic learning. All content is rooted in authentic Islamic teaching as understood through the Holy Quran and the example of the Prophet Muhammad &#65018;.",
  "terms.s16.diversity": "Differences in scholarly opinion across recognised schools of Islamic jurisprudence represent the natural and accepted diversity within Islamic scholarship. Content should be understood as educational and inspirational in nature, not as authoritative religious rulings.",
  "terms.s16.notFatwa": "Nuria content is not a substitute for qualified Islamic scholarly guidance. It is not a fatwa, ijtihad, or formal religious ruling. We encourage all users to consult qualified Islamic scholars or recognised Islamic institutions for:",
  "terms.s16.title": "16. Religious Content Disclaimer",
  "terms.s17.1.body": "The Family Deen Tree allows you to build a family graph, invite relatives, and record relationships and certain life events. Personal data. Names, relationships, dates, and optional progress indicators you choose to share. Is stored in Google Cloud Firestore and processed by Firebase Cloud Functions. The Family Deen Tree is limited to a maximum of six (6) linked members per family, matching the typical Apple Family Sharing / Google Play Family Library size. This cap is enforced server-side. Access may be tied to grandfathered Barakah entitlements as shown in the App. You will only add information about other persons where you have a lawful basis to do so (consent, family-purpose legitimate interest, etc.).",
  "terms.s17.1.title": "17.1 Family Deen Tree (Barakah)",
  "terms.s17.2.body": "Legacy bequests allow you to prepare text and voice messages intended for delivery to designated recipients, in accordance with rules shown in the App. Bequests are described as a \"white archive within Islam\". Cloud-synced spiritual and personal communications facilitated by software. Voice recordings are stored in Firebase Cloud Storage. Sealing a bequest may consume reflections. Delivery may be triggered by server-side logic after conditions you configure are met. Bequests are not wills, trusts, or other legally binding instruments unless separately executed under applicable law outside the App. They do not constitute legal proof of death, succession, or inheritance.",
  "terms.s17.2.title": "17.2 Legacy bequests (Barakah)",
  "terms.s17.3.body": "Halqa lets small groups form private circles and share limited spiritual progress within the circle. Membership, display names, and progress data are stored in Firestore. Halqa is not a general-purpose messaging service. You agree to treat other members respectfully and not to use Halqa to harass, abuse, or share unlawful content.",
  "terms.s17.3.title": "17.3 Halqa private circles",
  "terms.s17.4.body": "Muhasaba entries are stored only on your device (app preferences). They are not synchronised to our servers. Uninstalling the App without a full device backup may permanently remove Muhasaba entries.",
  "terms.s17.4.title": "17.4 Muhasaba self-accountability journal",
  "terms.s17.5.body": "Legacy Vault entries, Akhirah wishes, and timed messages are stored using your device's secure storage (Apple Keychain / Android encrypted preferences) and are not uploaded to Nuria servers solely by virtue of being saved.",
  "terms.s17.5.title": "17.5 Legacy Vault (on-device encrypted)",
  "terms.s17.6.body": "Nothing in the Family Deen Tree, legacy bequests, Halqa, Muhasaba, or Legacy Vault constitutes legal, financial, tax, estate-planning, medical, psychological, or formal Islamic legal (fiqh) advice. For matters with legal effect, consult qualified professionals.",
  "terms.s17.6.title": "17.6 No professional advice",
  "terms.s17.intro": "This section supplements Section 2 and references our Privacy Policy (in particular Sections 2.9 through 2.12).",
  "terms.s17.title": "17. Family Deen Tree, Legacy Bequests, Halqa, Muhasaba",
  "terms.s18.1.body": "Ask Nuria is the in-App Nuria companion feature that allows you to type a free-form question and receive a personalised answer grounded in authentic Islamic teaching. Technically, an automated language-model service generates the response under our system instructions and content filters; in the App and our marketing we refer to this experience as the Nuria companion and to the output as Nuria guidance. Ask Nuria is available to all Nuria users whose reflection balance permits a request (Section 6); it is not gated behind a subscription in the current ad-supported model.",
  "terms.s18.1.title": "18.1 Nature of the feature",
  "terms.s18.2.body": "Nuria guidance is not a fatwa, an Islamic legal ruling, or the formal opinion of a qualified scholar, mufti, or Islamic institution. It is intended for personal spiritual reflection and general Islamic learning. You must not rely on Nuria guidance as the basis for significant personal, legal, financial, medical, psychological, or religious decisions. For such matters consult a qualified Islamic scholar, healthcare professional, legal adviser, or other relevant professional.",
  "terms.s18.2.title": "18.2 Not a Sharia ruling, not a substitute for qualified scholarship",
  "terms.s18.3.intro": "Although we apply system-level prompting, content filtering, and quality review processes, the underlying language-model technology is inherently imperfect and may:",
  "terms.s18.3.title": "18.3 Accuracy and limitations",
  "terms.s18.3.verify": "We do not warrant that any specific Nuria guidance response is free from error or suitable for your individual circumstances. You should verify with qualified scholars before acting on guidance for important matters.",
  "terms.s18.4.fairUse": "Reflection-meter limits applicable to Ask Nuria are displayed in the App and apply to all users regardless of ad-free status.",
  "terms.s18.4.intro": "You may use Ask Nuria only to seek genuine personal spiritual guidance, Islamic knowledge, or religious reflection. You must not submit prompts that:",
  "terms.s18.4.title": "18.4 Acceptable use of Ask Nuria",
  "terms.s18.5.body": "Responses delivered to you are for your personal, private spiritual use only. You may not reproduce, publish, distribute, broadcast, sublicense, or commercialise them. We may use de-identified prompt and response data to monitor content quality and refine the feature, in accordance with our Privacy Policy.",
  "terms.s18.5.title": "18.5 Permitted use of responses",
  "terms.s18.title": "18. Ask Nuria. Nuria Guidance Disclaimer",
  "terms.s19.1.body": "The Qibla compass and prayer-time features require access to your device location. The App requests permission before activating them. Once granted, your device's GPS coordinates are used solely to calculate the direction to the Kaaba in Mecca and accurate prayer times for your position. All calculations are performed entirely on your device. Your GPS coordinates are never transmitted to our servers, never stored in your account, and never shared with any third party.",
  "terms.s19.1.title": "19.1 How these features work",
  "terms.s19.2.body": "You may revoke location permission at any time (iOS: Settings &rarr; Privacy & Security &rarr; Location Services &rarr; Nuria; Android: Settings &rarr; Apps &rarr; Nuria &rarr; Permissions &rarr; Location). Doing so disables Qibla and prayer times but does not affect other App functionality, your reflection balance, or your subscription.",
  "terms.s19.2.title": "19.2 Permission and revocation",
  "terms.s19.3.body": "Calculations depend on the quality of your device's GPS receiver and compass hardware. We do not guarantee precision in all conditions. For critical religious observance, verify prayer times through your local mosque or a trusted Islamic authority.",
  "terms.s19.3.title": "19.3 Accuracy",
  "terms.s19.title": "19. Location-Based Features (Qibla & Prayer Times)",
  "terms.s2.evolving": "The feature set of the App may expand, change, or be restructured over time. The definitive list of features available at any given moment is the one displayed in the App and in the applicable Apple App Store or Google Play listing. We will notify you of material changes in accordance with Section 26.",
  "terms.s2.foundation": "All content in the App is rooted in the Holy Quran, the teachings and example of the Prophet Muhammad &#65018;, and authentic Islamic scholarly tradition.",
  "terms.s2.intro": "Nuria is an Islamic companion application designed to support your daily spiritual life. The App is free to use with advertising; optional purchases can remove ads or add cosmetic benefits. Depending on the App version installed on your device, the App may deliver features including, but not limited to:",
  "terms.s2.title": "2. About Nuria",
  "terms.s20.intro": "To the fullest extent permitted by applicable law, and without prejudice to any mandatory statutory rights you may have as a consumer:",
  "terms.s20.mandatory": "Some jurisdictions do not allow the disclaimer of certain warranties, so some of the above disclaimers may not apply to you. Where mandatory consumer-protection or digital-content laws (including Swedish law and Directive (EU) 2019/770) provide implied warranties that cannot be excluded, those remain in force and nothing in these Terms is read to exclude them.",
  "terms.s20.title": "20. Disclaimer of Warranties",
  "terms.s21.carveouts": "Mandatory carve-outs. Nothing in these Terms limits or excludes our liability for:",
  "terms.s21.intro": "To the fullest extent permitted by applicable law:",
  "terms.s21.localLaw": "Some jurisdictions do not allow the exclusion or limitation of certain damages, so some limitations may not apply to you. Where local mandatory law gives you more favourable rights, those rights prevail.",
  "terms.s21.title": "21. Limitation of Liability",
  "terms.s22.control": "We may assume exclusive defence and control of any matter subject to indemnification by you, at our own expense; you will cooperate with our defence.",
  "terms.s22.intro": "To the extent permitted by applicable law, you agree to indemnify, defend, and hold harmless the Nuria Parties from and against any third-party claims, demands, damages, losses, liabilities, costs, and expenses (including reasonable legal fees) arising out of or relating to:",
  "terms.s22.title": "22. Indemnification",
  "terms.s23.1.body": "You may stop using the App and delete your account at any time. In the App: Settings &rarr; Account &rarr; Delete Account. Via web: nuria.one/delete-account. Or email hello@nuria.one from the address registered to your account. Deleting your Nuria account does not automatically cancel a subscription. You must cancel via Apple or Google as in Section 7.4.",
  "terms.s23.1.title": "23.1 Termination by you",
  "terms.s23.2.intro": "We may suspend or terminate your access to the App and your account, with or without prior notice, where:",
  "terms.s23.2.notice": "Where we suspend or terminate your account for breach, we will provide notice and the reason where reasonably possible, except where notification is prohibited by law or where the breach involves fraud or security risk that makes notification impracticable.",
  "terms.s23.2.title": "23.2 Suspension or termination by us",
  "terms.s23.3.title": "23.3 Effect of termination",
  "terms.s23.title": "23. Suspension and Termination",
  "terms.s24.bodies": "For consumer complaints or disputes that cannot be resolved directly with us:",
  "terms.s24.intro": "If you are a consumer resident in the European Union, the European Economic Area, the United Kingdom, or another jurisdiction with mandatory consumer-protection rules, you may have statutory rights that cannot be excluded or limited by these Terms. Nothing in these Terms is intended to restrict or supersede any statutory right you have as a consumer. Such rights include, without limitation:",
  "terms.s24.odrEmail": "Our email address for purposes of the EU ODR platform is hello@nuria.one.",
  "terms.s24.title": "24. Statutory Consumer Rights",
  "terms.s25.informal": "Before commencing formal proceedings, you agree to attempt to resolve any dispute informally by contacting us at hello@nuria.one. We will use good-faith efforts to resolve complaints within a 30-day informal negotiation period.",
  "terms.s25.jurisdiction": "If the dispute cannot be resolved informally, it shall be submitted to the non-exclusive jurisdiction of the Swedish courts, with the District Court of Gothenburg (Göteborgs tingsrätt) as the court of first instance for non-consumer matters. For consumers, mandatory consumer-protection law in your country of residence preserves your right to bring proceedings before a court in that country and to refer the dispute to a national consumer-dispute body; nothing in these Terms limits that right.",
  "terms.s25.law": "These Terms are governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of Sweden, without regard to its conflict-of-law principles. The United Nations Convention on Contracts for the International Sale of Goods (CISG) does not apply.",
  "terms.s25.noArbitration": "No mandatory arbitration. We do not require consumers to submit to mandatory binding arbitration, and we do not waive any consumer's right to bring proceedings in a court of competent jurisdiction.",
  "terms.s25.title": "25. Governing Law, Jurisdiction, and Dispute Resolution",
  "terms.s26.acceptance": "Your continued use of the App after the notified effective date of any revised Terms constitutes acceptance. If you do not accept the revised Terms, you must stop using the App before the effective date and, if applicable, cancel any active subscription through Apple or Google.",
  "terms.s26.intro": "We may update these Terms to reflect changes in applicable law, our business practices, the features of the App, or for any other legitimate reason. The \"Last updated\" date at the top of this page reflects the most recent revision.",
  "terms.s26.material": "For material adverse changes (changes that could significantly reduce your rights or increase your obligations), we will give you at least 30 days' advance notice by means of: (a) updating the \"Last updated\" date, (b) displaying a prominent in-App notice at your next login, and (c) sending an email to your registered email address where required by law or where the change materially affects your legal rights. You may cancel any active subscription before the change takes effect.",
  "terms.s26.nonMaterial": "For non-material changes (editorial clarifications, corrections, additions that do not restrict your rights), changes take effect immediately upon posting.",
  "terms.s26.title": "26. Changes to These Terms",
  "terms.s27.body": "We will not be liable for any failure or delay in performing our obligations to the extent such failure or delay is caused by events beyond our reasonable control, including: acts of God, natural disasters, pandemics, war, terrorism, civil unrest, government actions, embargoes, strikes, labour disputes, fire, flood, infrastructure outages affecting Apple, Google, Firebase, Google Cloud, or other upstream service providers, telecommunications or internet failures, cybersecurity incidents, and denial-of-service attacks.",
  "terms.s27.title": "27. Force Majeure",
  "terms.s28.body": "You may not assign or transfer these Terms or any rights or obligations hereunder without our prior written consent. We may assign or transfer these Terms, in whole or in part, without restriction, including in connection with a merger, acquisition, corporate reorganisation, sale of assets, or transfer to an affiliate, provided that your rights are not materially diminished except as permitted by these Terms and applicable law.",
  "terms.s28.title": "28. Assignment",
  "terms.s29.consent": "Electronic communications consent. By using the App you consent to electronic delivery of agreements, disclosures, notices, and other communications. You agree that all such electronic communications satisfy any legal requirement that they be in writing, to the extent permitted by applicable law.",
  "terms.s29.from": "We may give you notices in connection with these Terms by email to the address registered to your account or via in-App banners and messages. Such notices are deemed given when sent or displayed.",
  "terms.s29.title": "29. Notices and Electronic Communications",
  "terms.s29.to": "You may give us notices by email to hello@nuria.one with a subject line clearly identifying the matter (for example \"Notice. Terms of Service. Section 23 termination\").",
  "terms.s3.family": "If you are the holder of an Apple ID or Google account used by family members (including under Apple Family Sharing or Google Play Family Library), you remain solely responsible for any purchases, subscriptions, or trial activations made under that account, including by minors. You are responsible for setting appropriate parental controls (Apple Screen Time, Google Family Link) and for ensuring that any minor's use of the App complies with these Terms.",
  "terms.s3.minimum": "To use Nuria you must be at least 13 years of age. If you are between 13 and the age of majority in your jurisdiction, you confirm that you have obtained the consent of a parent or legal guardian to use the App and to accept these Terms.",
  "terms.s3.purchaser": "If you wish to make any in-app purchase (including Nuria Serene, Nuria Noor, reflection top-ups, donations, or legacy subscription products where still available), you must additionally be the legal age required to enter into a binding contract in your country of residence, and you must be the holder of, or have express permission to use, the Apple ID or Google account from which the purchase is made.",
  "terms.s3.title": "3. Eligibility, Minors, and Family Accounts",
  "terms.s3.under13": "The App is not intended for, and we do not knowingly permit access by, persons under 13. If we discover that a person under 13 has created an account, we will terminate it and delete associated data promptly, in accordance with our Privacy Policy.",
  "terms.s30.1.body": "If any provision of these Terms is found by a court or competent authority to be invalid or unenforceable under applicable law, that provision will be modified to the minimum extent necessary to make it valid, or. If modification is not possible. Severed from these Terms. The remaining provisions continue in full force and effect.",
  "terms.s30.1.title": "30.1 Severability",
  "terms.s30.2.body": "Our failure or delay in exercising or enforcing any right or remedy is not a waiver of that right or remedy, nor does it prevent us from enforcing it later. A waiver is effective only if given in writing and signed by an authorised representative.",
  "terms.s30.2.title": "30.2 No waiver",
  "terms.s30.3.body": "Provisions that by their nature should survive termination. Payment obligations, intellectual property, user-generated content licence, content disclaimers, warranty disclaimers, limitation of liability, indemnification, governing law, jurisdiction, and dispute resolution. Survive termination of these Terms.",
  "terms.s30.3.title": "30.3 Survival",
  "terms.s30.4.body": "Section headings are for convenience only and do not affect interpretation.",
  "terms.s30.4.title": "30.4 Headings",
  "terms.s30.5.body": "These Terms are originally drafted in English. Translations are provided as a convenience; in case of conflict, the English version controls, to the extent permitted by mandatory local consumer law.",
  "terms.s30.5.title": "30.5 Language",
  "terms.s30.title": "30. Severability, Waiver, Survival, Headings, Language",
  "terms.s31.body": "These Terms, together with our Privacy Policy and any feature-specific terms or in-App notices we display, constitute the entire agreement between you and OakDev concerning your use of the App and supersede all prior or contemporaneous agreements, representations, warranties, or understandings. Oral or written. Relating to the same subject matter. In the event of an inconsistency between these Terms and feature-specific terms displayed in the App, the feature-specific terms prevail to the extent of the inconsistency for that specific feature only.",
  "terms.s31.title": "31. Entire Agreement",
  "terms.s32.1.body": "By downloading, installing, creating an account, making an in-app purchase, or otherwise using the App you accept these Terms. If you do not accept these Terms, do not use the App.",
  "terms.s32.1.title": "32.1 Acceptance",
  "terms.s32.2.body": "Your download or use of the App is also subject to the then-current terms, rules, and policies of the platform from which you obtained the App. Where they conflict with these Terms regarding the App, the platform terms govern only to the extent of the conflict and only with respect to your relationship with that platform.",
  "terms.s32.2.title": "32.2 Third-party platforms (Apple and Google)",
  "terms.s32.3.body": "You represent that you are not located in a country subject to a Swedish, EU, UN, or US government embargo or designated as a terrorist-supporting region, and that you are not on any government list of prohibited or restricted parties. You must not use the App in violation of export-control or sanctions laws.",
  "terms.s32.3.title": "32.3 Sanctions, export, and restricted users",
  "terms.s32.4.body": "Nothing in these Terms creates a partnership, agency, joint venture, or employment relationship between you and OakDev.",
  "terms.s32.4.title": "32.4 Independent contractors",
  "terms.s32.title": "32. Miscellaneous Legal Terms",
  "terms.s33.1.body": "Nuria Suq (the \"Suq\") is an optional in-App marketplace where community members offer halal goods, skills, and services and exchange them with each other through free barter arrangements called Tabaddul exchanges. No money is paid through the App for an exchange, and Nuria processes no payments for exchanges. Nuria provides the venue only. We are not a party to any exchange between users, and we give no warranty of any kind for the performance, quality, safety, legality, or completion of any exchange. Any agreement formed through the Suq exists solely between the participating users.",
  "terms.s33.1.title": "33.1 A venue for free barter exchanges",
  "terms.s33.2.body": "Before you can create a seller profile, publish a listing, propose an exchange, write a review, or send a message in the Suq, the App requires you to accept the marketplace community rules. Those rules form part of these Terms. If you do not accept them, the Suq features remain unavailable to you while the rest of the App continues to work normally.",
  "terms.s33.2.title": "33.2 Acceptance of the marketplace rules",
  "terms.s33.3.intro": "Only halal goods, skills, and services may be offered or requested in the Suq. Without limiting Section 13, you must not publish or send content in the Suq that involves or promotes:",
  "terms.s33.3.scope": "These rules apply equally to listings, seller profiles, exchange proposals, reviews, and private messages.",
  "terms.s33.3.title": "33.3 Content rules",
  "terms.s33.4.body": "All content you publish or send through the Suq, including listings, listing photos, seller profiles, exchange proposals, reviews, and private messages, is automatically checked by AI safety systems and may additionally be reviewed by our staff. Content that is flagged can be hidden or removed. Accounts responsible for repeated violations, or for violent or extremist content, can be restricted or suspended in accordance with Section 23. Where required by law, we may refer serious safety threats to the competent authorities.",
  "terms.s33.4.title": "33.4 Automated and human moderation",
  "terms.s33.5.body": "The App provides tools to report Suq content and to block other users. When you block a user, that user can no longer contact you through the Suq.",
  "terms.s33.5.title": "33.5 Reporting and blocking",
  "terms.s33.6.body": "Reviews must reflect a genuine exchange that you have completed through the Suq. Fabricated, incentivised, retaliatory, or misleading reviews are prohibited and may be removed.",
  "terms.s33.6.title": "33.6 Reviews",
  "terms.s33.7.body": "How personal data is processed for Suq moderation, including the automated safety checks applied to private messages, is described in our Privacy Policy.",
  "terms.s33.7.title": "33.7 Moderation data",
  "terms.s33.title": "33. Nuria Suq Marketplace, Tabaddul Exchanges, and Messages",
  "terms.s34.intro": "For any questions, concerns, or formal notices relating to these Terms of Service, contact us:",
  "terms.s34.sla": "We aim to acknowledge written enquiries within 2 business days and to resolve substantive matters within 30 days.",
  "terms.s34.title": "34. Contact",
  "terms.s4.intro": "To use the App you must create a Nuria account using a valid email address (or a supported sign-in provider). You agree to:",
  "terms.s4.oneAccount": "You may not create more than one Nuria account per person. Creating multiple accounts to circumvent suspension, access restrictions, starter-grant limits (see Section 5.5), or to exploit any promotional or referral programme is prohibited.",
  "terms.s4.refusal": "We reserve the right to refuse registration, or to suspend or terminate an account, at our reasonable discretion, including where we suspect fraud, abuse of starter-reflection or legacy-trial mechanics, multiple-account creation, reflection-balance manipulation, rewarded-ad fraud, payment-instrument fraud, or any other violation of these Terms.",
  "terms.s4.title": "4. Your Account",
  "terms.s5.1.body": "Nuria is free to download and free to use. Creating a Nuria account and using core App features does not require a subscription. The free service is supported by third-party advertising displayed in the App (Section 5.3). You may optionally purchase one-time products to remove ads permanently (Section 7.1) or buy reflection top-ups and donations (Sections 6 and 8).",
  "terms.s5.1.title": "5.1 Ad-supported free model",
  "terms.s5.2.intro": "Unless otherwise stated in the App at the time of use, free users have access to the full Nuria feature set. Including the Holy Quran, prayer tools, Nuria Qaida, Sunnat library, daily content, personalization, Ask Nuria (subject to your reflection balance), tafsir, widgets, Halqa, Muhasaba, and other features described in Section 2. Monetisation of the free tier is provided through advertising, not through locking core religious content behind a paywall.",
  "terms.s5.2.title": "5.2 What is included for free",
  "terms.s5.3.intro": "Unless you are ad-free (Section 7.1 or a grandfathered subscriber), the App displays third-party advertisements through Google AdMob, including banner, native, interstitial, and rewarded formats. By using the free App you acknowledge that:",
  "terms.s5.3.title": "5.3 Advertising in the App",
  "terms.s5.4.body": "Before you confirm any in-app purchase, the App store interface and the App present the title, price, type (one-time non-consumable, consumable, or auto-renewing subscription for legacy products), and what the purchase provides. For legacy auto-renewing subscriptions still held by existing subscribers, the store also presents the subscription period, auto-renewal terms, and trial terms where applicable. Functional links to these Terms and our Privacy Policy are shown at account creation and in purchase flows.",
  "terms.s5.4.title": "5.4 Pre-purchase disclosures (required by Apple 3.1.2 and Google Play)",
  "terms.s5.5.body": "To prevent abuse of free starter reflections (and legacy free-trial mechanics where still applicable), we enforce one starter grant per device and maintain device-binding / fingerprint anti-abuse records as described in our Privacy Policy. Attempts to bypass these measures (resetting devices, emulators, rotating accounts) may result in suspension or termination per Section 23.",
  "terms.s5.5.title": "5.5 Anti-abuse. Starter reflections and legacy trial limits",
  "terms.s5.6.body": "Users who enrolled in Nuria's previous subscription model may still hold active Standard or Barakah subscriptions with an introductory trial phase governed by Apple or Google. Those trials auto-convert to paid subscriptions unless cancelled through the App Store or Google Play at least 24 hours before the trial ends. New users are not required to start such a trial to use Nuria. Legacy subscription terms are in Section 7.5.",
  "terms.s5.6.title": "5.6 Legacy subscription trial (existing subscribers only)",
  "terms.s5.title": "5. Access to the App. Free with Ads and Optional Purchases",
  "terms.s6.1.body": "\"Reflections\" are digital units used within the App to request personalised spiritual content. Reflections are not currency, have no monetary value, cannot be exchanged for cash or any other goods or services, are non-transferable between accounts, and (other than through the trial, paid subscription renewals, top-up products, or promotional grants described below) cannot be obtained from Nuria.",
  "terms.s6.1.title": "6.1 What reflections are",
  "terms.s6.2.additive": "Reflection grants are generally additive where applicable. Legacy subscribers who convert from a trial may retain unused trial reflections into their first paid renewal cycle in accordance with the catalog rules active at enrolment.",
  "terms.s6.2.title": "6.2 How you obtain reflections",
  "terms.s6.3.body": "Each request for a personalised reflection from any category deducts one (1) reflection from your balance at the moment the reflection is generated. If the App returns an error before the reflection is successfully delivered, the reflection will be restored to your balance within a reasonable time. For legacy subscribers, unused reflections may carry over between renewal periods while the subscription remains continuously active; if a legacy subscription lapses, unused reflections may expire 30 days after the subscription end date, as displayed in the App. Free users retain unused purchased or earned reflections until consumed, subject to account status.",
  "terms.s6.3.title": "6.3 How reflections are used and carry-over",
  "terms.s6.4.body": "Reflections that have been consumed are non-refundable. Unused reflections forfeited upon account deletion are non-refundable, except to the extent required by mandatory applicable consumer law.",
  "terms.s6.4.title": "6.4 Non-refundability",
  "terms.s6.5.body": "Your current reflection balance is displayed within the App. If you believe there is an error, please contact hello@nuria.one and we will investigate promptly.",
  "terms.s6.5.title": "6.5 Balance display and corrections",
  "terms.s6.title": "6. Reflections and Your Balance",
  "terms.s7.1.intro": "Nuria offers two one-time, non-consumable purchases that permanently remove advertising:",
  "terms.s7.1.regional": "Prices vary by region; Apple and Google handle local-currency pricing and taxes. These purchases do not auto-renew. Ad-free status is tied to your Nuria account after server-side verification. You may restore these purchases on a new device through Restore Purchases (Section 10).",
  "terms.s7.1.title": "7.1 Nuria Serene and Nuria Noor (current primary paid products)",
  "terms.s7.2.preamble": "As of the effective date of these Terms, all core App features are available to free users, monetised through advertising (Section 5). Paid products change your experience as follows:",
  "terms.s7.2.title": "7.2 Free tier vs paid benefits",
  "terms.s7.3.intro": "Nuria previously sold two subscription tiers (Standard and Barakah) in monthly and annual billing periods. These products are no longer the primary way to access Nuria, but we continue to honour active subscriptions and process renewals for existing subscribers:",
  "terms.s7.3.title": "7.3 Legacy subscriptions. Standard and Barakah (not sold as primary access)",
  "terms.s7.4.android": "Android (Google Play)",
  "terms.s7.4.androidNote": "Or visit play.google.com/store/account/subscriptions in a browser.",
  "terms.s7.4.ios": "iOS (Apple ID)",
  "terms.s7.4.iosNote": "Alternatively, open the App Store, tap your profile icon, tap Subscriptions, and proceed as above.",
  "terms.s7.4.timing": "After cancellation, your tier benefits remain active until the end of the current paid period. No partial refunds are issued by Nuria for the unused portion of a cancelled period, subject to Apple's / Google's refund policies and any mandatory consumer rights described in Section 24.",
  "terms.s7.4.title": "7.4 Auto-renewal and billing (legacy subscriptions only)",
  "terms.s7.5.intro": "You can manage or cancel a legacy Nuria subscription at any time via the platform on which it was purchased. The App provides deep-links to the relevant settings screen; the steps are:",
  "terms.s7.5.title": "7.5 Manage and cancel legacy subscriptions. Apple and Google",
  "terms.s7.6.body": "Changes between plans within the same subscription group. For example, upgrading from Standard to Barakah, downgrading from Barakah to Standard, or switching from monthly to annual billing. Are handled entirely by the App store:",
  "terms.s7.6.guarantee": "As a result, you never pay twice for overlapping coverage: any unused paid time on your previous plan is credited by the store at the moment of change. We have no ability to override this. The App store is the system of record for plan changes and proration.",
  "terms.s7.6.title": "7.6 Plan changes mid-cycle (store-handled proration)",
  "terms.s7.7.intro": "When a legacy subscription ends (cancellation, non-renewal, or payment failure):",
  "terms.s7.7.title": "7.7 Effect of legacy subscription cancellation or lapse",
  "terms.s7.title": "7. One-Time Purchases and Legacy Subscriptions",
  "terms.s8.1.body": "All payments for Nuria Serene, Nuria Noor, reflection top-ups, donations, legacy subscriptions, Hiba gifts, and any other paid digital features offered within Nuria are processed exclusively by Apple Inc. (Apple App Store, for iOS users) or by Google LLC (Google Play, for Android users). Nuria does not charge you directly, does not process your payment card or banking information, does not store your financial data, and does not have access to your payment credentials. Your purchase is governed by your agreement with Apple or Google and their respective billing terms.",
  "terms.s8.1.title": "8.1 Exclusive platform billing",
  "terms.s8.2.body": "The price of each product is displayed in the App and in the applicable store listing in the currency of your store account at the time of purchase. Prices vary by region due to local currency, applicable taxes, and store pricing tiers. Apple and Google collect and remit any applicable taxes (VAT, GST, digital services tax, etc.) on purchases made through their platforms. We reserve the right to change subscription pricing at any time for future periods; where required, Apple or Google will notify you in advance and obtain any required acceptance before the new price takes effect for your subscription.",
  "terms.s8.2.title": "8.2 Pricing, taxes, and price changes",
  "terms.s8.3.consumed": "Reflections that have already been consumed are non-refundable as the service has been delivered. Granted but unconsumed reflections are non-refundable upon cancellation, except where mandatory consumer-protection law requires otherwise.",
  "terms.s8.3.intro": "Because all payments are processed by Apple or Google, Nuria does not directly refund payments, except where required by mandatory consumer-protection law. Refund requests must be submitted to the relevant store:",
  "terms.s8.3.title": "8.3 Refunds. Handled by Apple and Google",
  "terms.s8.4.body": "If you are a consumer resident in the European Union or the European Economic Area, you have a 14-day right of withdrawal for distance contracts for digital content and digital services under Directive 2011/83/EU. Important: under Article 16(m) of that Directive (and its national implementations), the right of withdrawal is lost once you start consuming the digital content with your express prior consent and acknowledgement that the right is thereby waived. Which typically occurs the moment you use purchased reflections, activate a legacy subscription or trial, or receive the benefit of a one-time purchase (such as ad removal). Using the free ad-supported App without purchasing does not by itself waive withdrawal rights for any future paid purchase. Where applicable consumer law in your country grants additional or different rights, those rights are preserved (see Section 24).",
  "terms.s8.4.title": "8.4 EU consumer-law statutory rights",
  "terms.s8.title": "8. Billing, Payments, and Refunds",
  "terms.s9.1.body": "\"Hiba\" (هبة, gift) is a one-time gift purchase that allows you (the \"Buyer\") to give a designated recipient (the \"Recipient\") one (1) year of Barakah tier access. The Hiba product identifier is nuria_hiba_yearly_gift. The price is set by Apple or Google in your local currency and presented at checkout.",
  "terms.s9.1.title": "9.1 What Hiba is",
  "terms.s9.2.title": "9.2 How Hiba works",
  "terms.s9.3.title": "9.3 Limitations and refunds for Hiba",
  "terms.s9.title": "9. Hiba Gift Subscriptions"
}